data.name: Masala Dosa
data.quickTastyDescription: Crispy rice and lentil crepes filled with a spiced potato filling, served with chutney and sambar.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a pan, heat a little oil and add mustard seeds. Once they splutter, add curry leaves, green chilies, and chopped onions. Saut√© until onions are translucent.
Add the mashed potatoes, turmeric powder, and salt. Mix well and cook for a few minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.
Heat a non-stick skillet on medium heat. Pour a ladleful of dosa batter onto the skillet and spread it in a circular motion to form a thin pancake.
Drizzle a little oil around the edges and cook until the dosa is golden brown and crispy.
Place a spoonful of the potato filling in the center of the dosa, fold it over, and serve hot with chutney and sambar.
data.detailedName: Crispy Masala Dosa with Spiced Potato Filling
